<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10630&amp;p=120076#p120076"><![CDATA[
Hi, I was looking for a donor cart to solder a rom socket so I could test my NROM games... I looked inside a pirate fami cartridge, and since I saw a package-like chip, I opened the cart. It's a pretty board for what I can tell, since there's a 6264LD + PAL16L8ACN (pirated mapper?) plus a 3V Panasonic CR2032 battery (SRAM?!?)... however there was no ROM to be found except for these stupid globtops (three). Interestingly enough there's a circuit line near the center globtop marked &quot;VCR7&quot;... is that what I think it is?<br /><br />So anyway, my question is: is it possible to do something with this cart to accept an EPROM? Is there a way to melt this globtops away?<br /><br />thanks.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5877">Punch</a> — Wed Oct 30, 2013 10:05 pm</p><hr />
